  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Rustic Black sits in the heart of the gray spectrum for Heritage. It reads as a clean charcoal in direct sun and softens to a near-black on cloudy or shaded elevations. That tonal range is the reason it dominates the dimensional asphalt category nationally.",
      "The granule blend uses a base of charcoal granules with smaller portions of true black and storm-gray accents to keep the surface from going dead flat. In direct midday sun the texture catches enough light to show the dimensional shadow line that gives Heritage its premium feel.",
      "Pairs cleanly with white, cream, navy, sage, and warm terra-cotta sidings. Almost any house color works underneath it."
    ],
